textBody:
Martin Luther King Jr. (1929–1968) was a minister and Civil Rights activist.

Martin Luther King may also refer to:
*Martin Luther King Sr., Baptist minister and father of Martin Luther King Jr.
*Martin Luther King III, son of Martin Luther King Jr. and a former head of the Southern Christian Leadership Conference
* Martin Luther King, Jr. (Wilson), a 1986 public artwork by American sculptor John Wilson
